terminal_based.name: Claude Code
key_features: Build features from natural language descriptions.
Debug and fix issues from error messages.
Automate tasks like fixing lint issues and writing release notes.
Can take actions like editing files, running commands, and creating commits.
Enterprise-ready (can be self-hosted on AWS or GCP).
terminal_based.pricing_model: Based on API token consumption. Average cost of ~$6 per developer per day. Average monthly cost of ~$100-200 per developer per month with Sonnet 4. Usage included for Pro and Max plan users.

qualitative_assessment.ease_of_use: High (for developers comfortable with the command line)
qualitative_assessment.onboarding_experience: Very easy, with a clear 'Get started in 30 seconds' guide in the official documentation.

terminal_based.name: Qwen CLI
terminal_based.pricing_model: Based on API key usage from Alibaba Cloud or third-party services like OpenRouter.

terminal_based.name: LogiQCLI

terminal_based.pricing_model: Pay-as-you-go model for data that exceeds the daily volume limit of a customer's plan. The price is based on the plan's cost per 1GB of overage plus a 40% additional charge. Specific pricing requires contacting a sales representative.

qualitative_assessment.ease_of_use: High (rated 8.8/10 on G2Crowd for the Logz.io platform). The AI Agent uses natural language queries.
qualitative_assessment.documentation_quality: High, with clear and comprehensive official documentation.
qualitative_assessment.onboarding_experience: Very easy for existing Logz.io users, accessible with a single button click in the platform.

ide_embedded.name: Amazon CodeGuru

Provides recommendations on how to fix identified vulnerabilities.
Tracks the status of vulnerabilities until closure.
Includes CodeGuru Profiler for finding an application's most expensive lines of code.
ide_embedded.pricing_model: CodeGuru Security is free in public preview. CodeGuru Reviewer and Profiler have free tiers and paid plans based on usage.

ide_embedded.name: DeepCode AI
key_features: Identifies security vulnerabilities and quality issues.
Simplified rules creation with DeepCode AI Search.
supported_models: Multiple fine-tuned AI models (hybrid of symbolic and generative AI)
ide_embedded.pricing_model: Free plan with limited tests. Paid plans (Team and Enterprise) with more features and higher limits, starting at $25/month per contributing developer.

ide_embedded.name: SQLAI.ai
key_features: AI-powered SQL generator that can generate, optimize, validate, simplify, and explain SQL queries.
Can connect to data sources to increase accuracy.
Has a query converter to migrate queries between database engines.
Can optimize databases with database indexes.
ide_embedded.pricing_model: Free trial, with paid plans (Explorer, Pro, Pro XL) starting at $6/month.

ide_embedded.name: AskCodi
key_features: AI coding assistant with a wide range of tools, including a code generator, refactorer, fixer, and translator.

ide_embedded.pricing_model: Free plan with limited features. Paid plans (Premium and Ultimate) with more features and higher limits, starting at $149.99/year.

ide_embedded.name: Sourcegraph Cody

Chat, autocomplete, and inline edit features.
ide_embedded.pricing_model: Enterprise-focused, with a 'Talk to sales' option. No public pricing for individuals.

ide_embedded.name: Android Studio Bot

Helps generate code, answer questions about Android development, and fix errors.
Leverages Codey, Google's foundation model for coding, which is a descendant of PaLM 2.

ide_embedded.name: CodeWP
key_features: AI chat and coding tools trained specifically for WordPress.
Can create accurate, complex WordPress plugins and code snippets.
Can troubleshoot and fix fatal errors.
Has a community where users can share snippets.
ide_embedded.pricing_model: Free plan with limited actions. Paid plans (Pro and Agency) with more features and higher limits, starting at $18/month.

ide_embedded.name: Replit AI

Can build an app from a screenshot.

ide_embedded.name: Amazon CodeWhisperer
